The paper focuses on using a fully convolutional network (FCN) to extract minutiae from latent fingerprints. This involves learning features directly from data to overcome complex background noises. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves using a convolutional neural network (CNN) to reclassify minutiae and calculate their orientations, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of a FCN and CNN also involves machine learning, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves fingerprint identification, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves visualizing the trained model, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
